            <li>‚Ä¢ You need to launch quickly and iterate fast</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want AI generation with regeneration feature</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You need multilingual support (international business)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You prefer HTML/CSS export over React code</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You need built-in ecommerce functionality</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You're not a designer and don't need pixel perfection</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-cyan-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-cyan-50/50 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-cyan-600 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm mb-3">Choose Framer if:</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Design quality is your top priority</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You're building a portfolio or visual-heavy site</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You know React and want React code export</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You have time to refine and perfect the design</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You work in design/creative industries</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Maximum design flexibility matters more than speed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <div class="mb-12 mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">FAQ: Dorik vs Framer</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Is Dorik's regen feature really that useful?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, it's the standout feature. Instead of manually editing copy for hours, you click "Regenerate Section" and get AI-generated alternatives in 30 seconds. Test: hero section took 2 hours to perfect in Framer (manual edits). Dorik took 3 minutes (2 regen clicks). For landing pages where copy matters, regen saves hours.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I export code from both platforms?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, but different formats. Dorik exports clean HTML/CSS/JS that works anywhere - perfect for non-developers. Framer exports React/JSX code - powerful if you know React, meaningless if you don't. Developers prefer Framer's export. Everyone else prefers Dorik's.</p>
        </div>

